{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_black_pixels = get_non_black_pixels(input_grid)\n    smallest_rect = find_smallest_rect(non_black_pixels, input_grid)\n    output_grid = duplicate_smallest_rect(smallest_rect)\n    return output_grid\ndef duplicate_smallest_rect(smallest_rect: Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the smallest rectangle that contains all non-black pixels in the input grid and the input grid itself,\n    duplicates the smallest rectangle in the right of it and returns the resulting grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - smallest_rect (Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]): A tuple of tuples representing the top-left and bottom-right coordinates of the smallest rectangle that contains all non-black pixels.\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array representing the resulting grid after duplicating the smallest rectangle in the right of it.\n    \"\"\"\n    top_left, bottom_right = smallest_rect\n    width = bottom_right[1] - top_left[1] + 1\n    height = bottom_right[0] - top_left[0] + 1\n    output_grid = np.zeros((height, width * 2), dtype=np.int32)\n    for i in range(top_left[0], bottom_right[0] + 1):\n        for j in range(top_left[1], bottom_right[1] + 1):\n            output_grid[i - top_left[0]][j - top_left[1]] = input_grid[i][j]\n            output_grid[i - top_left[0]][j - top_left[1] + width] = input_grid[i][j]\n    return output_grid\ndef find_smallest_rect(non_black_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the input grid and the input grid itself,\n    returns a tuple of tuples representing the top-left and bottom-right coordinates of the smallest rectangle that contains all non-black pixels.\n\n    Args:\n    - non_black_pixels (List[Tuple[int, int]]): A list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the input grid.\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    - Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]: A tuple of tuples representing the top-left and bottom-right coordinates of the smallest rectangle that contains all non-black pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    min_x, min_y = (float('inf'), float('inf'))\n    max_x, max_y = (float('-inf'), float('-inf'))\n    for pixel in non_black_pixels:\n        x, y = pixel\n        min_x = min(min_x, x)\n        min_y = min(min_y, y)\n        max_x = max(max_x, x)\n        max_y = max(max_y, y)\n    return ((min_x, min_y), (max_x, max_y))\ndef get_non_black_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    - List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_black_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] != black:\n                non_black_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return non_black_pixels", "user_code": "def main(input_grid:np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_black_pixels = `get the non_black_pixels in the input_grid`(input_grid)\n    smallest_rect = `find the smallest_rect which contains all of these non_black_pixels in the input_grid`(non_black_pixels, input_grid)\n    output_grid = `duplicate the smallest_rect in the right of it`(smallest_rect)\n    return output_grid", "gpt_code": "def duplicate_smallest_rect(smallest_rect: Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the smalles