{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_black_pixels = get_non_black_pixels(input_grid)\n    smallest_rect = find_smallest_rect(non_black_pixels, input_grid)\n    output_grid = np.concatenate([smallest_rect, smallest_rect])\n    return output_grid\ndef find_smallest_rect(non_black_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the input grid and the input grid,\n    returns the smallest rectangle which contains all of these non-black pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    non_black_pixels: A list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the input grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the smallest rectangle which contains all of these non-black pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    min_x = min([x for x, y in non_black_pixels])\n    max_x = max([x for x, y in non_black_pixels])\n    min_y = min([y for x, y in non_black_pixels])\n    max_y = max([y for x, y in non_black_pixels])\n    smallest_rect = input_grid[min_x:max_x + 1, min_y:max_y + 1]\n    return smallest_rect\ndef get_non_black_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the coordinates of all non-black pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_black_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] != black:\n                non_black_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return non_black_pixels", "user_code": "def main(input_grid:np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_black_pixels = `get the non_black_pixels in the input_grid`(in